name: auroral-electrojet-indices-designed-to-provide-a-global-measure-2-5-minute-intervals-of-auroral
notes:
The Auroral Electrojet index (AE) is designed to provide a global quantitative measure of auroral zone magnetic activity produced by enhanced ionospheric currents flowing below and within the auroral oval. Ideally, it is the total range of deviation at an instant of time from quiet day values of the horizontal magnetic field (H) around the auroral oval. The indices are derived in response to a need voiced by scientific users. These indices are computed from a
                    network of geomagnetic observatories, some recording digitally and others as analog, which encircle the northern auroral zone. The AE computation uses horizontal magnetic field values measured at 2.5-minute intervals. AE plus the supplemental indices AL, AU and AO are included in this data file.
